MORNING REPORT: POP/ROCK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Concert Crashers: A group of about 40 youths scaled gates at the Shoreline 
Amphitheater in Mountain View, Calif., during a performance Friday by the rap 
group Public Enemy and randomly assaulted concertgoers and security guards. 
</P>
<P>
Thirty people were treated for minor injuries at the venue's first-aid 
stations, said police Lt. Gary Smith. Victims told police that they believed 
the attackers were members of a gang, but Smith said no gang affiliation had 
been confirmed. The assaults, which took place in the plaza surrounding the 
amphitheater, apparently did not disrupt the concert attended by 8,000 people. 
BETH KLEID 
