<P>
Bandit Stops News: WLS-TV in Chicago returned to broadcasting Sunday after 
nearly nine hours of dead air caused by the search for a pizzeria bandit who 
slipped into the station's building. 
</P>
<P>
It was "business as usual" for the ABC station once it resumed broadcasting at 
7 a.m. after three searches of its location failed to locate the gunman, 
General Manager Joe Ahern said. The station was evacuated just before 
Saturday's 10 p.m. newscast. The gunman, suspected in a robbery Saturday of a 
Chicago pizzeria, was fleeing police when he entered the building housing the 
studios. BETH KLEID 
