<HEADLINE>
<P>
IRAQI EMBASSY IN BONN CALLED ARMS DEAL CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BONN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Iraqi Embassy in Bonn served as a nerve center for illegal weapons deals 
between West German companies and Iraq, a West German weekly news magazine 
reported Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
Der Spiegel said that confiscated business files from companies allegedly 
involved in the illegal arms scam showed that weapons dealers were frequent 
visitors to the embassy. 
</P>
