<HEADLINE>
<P>
FRANCE, DJIBOUTI HOLD TALKS ON GULF CRISIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DJIBOUTI 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
French Defense Minister Jean-Pierre Chevenement held Persian Gulf crisis talks 
with Djibouti Prime Minister Barkat Gourad Hamadou, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
The talks Saturday followed reinforcement of French military and naval forces 
in the region. France maintains a military force in this former French colony 
at the mouth of the Red Sea with the agreement of the Djibouti government. 
</P>
<P>
Chevenement also reviewed French forces assembling here for possible action in 
the crisis, military sources said. 
