LOPEZ WILL MEET RAMOS IN MAIN EVENT TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ben Lopez, the California super featherweight champion, takes on Pablo Ramos in 
a non-title defense tonight in the main event of the monthly boxing program at 
the Irvine Marriott. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez (15-5), of Ontario, has 10 knockouts. Ramos, of Mexico City, has a 20-8 
record with 12 knockouts. 
</P>
<P>
Jesus Castenada of La Habra and Ernie Magdalena of Westminster, both light 
heavyweights, square off in the six-round semi-main event. 
</P>
<P>
The first of six scheduled bouts starts at 7:30. Tickets go on sale at 10 a.m. 
in the hotel's grand ballroom. 
