NEWLYWED SETS HIMSELF AFIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
INDIANAPOLIS 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A newlywed who had threatened to kill himself during fights with his young 
bride set himself on fire after an argument with her, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
Marion County Sheriff's Sgt. William Newman said Michael Pierce, 26, suffered 
burns over 85% of his body and was in critical condition early today in Wishard 
Memorial Hospital. 
</P>
<P>
Newman said Pierce threatened suicide while arguing with his wife, Kathy. Mrs. 
Pierce said she heard a "poof" moments after her husband walked outside her 
grandparents' home and got into his car. 
</P>
<P>
Pierce was on fire when he jumped out of the car but it was not immediately 
known how he set himself ablaze. Newman said the couple married July 24 after a 
three-month courtship. 
