EARNINGS; 
</P>
<P>
ROSS STORES INCOME FALLS 29.6% 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEWARK, Calif. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Discount clothing retailer Ross Stores Inc. said today net income dropped 29.6% 
in the second quarter to $5 million, or 21 cents a share, from $7.1 million, or 
30 cents a share, a year ago. 
</P>
<P>
Sales grew to $193.2 million from $175.6 million in the year-earlier quarter. 
Stores open more than a year posted flat sales from last year's second quarter. 
</P>
<P>
For the six months ended Aug. 4, net income dropped 37.5% to $6.6 million, or 
28 cents a share, from $10.5 million, or 43 cents a share, in the comparable 
period of 1989. 
</P>
<P>
Sales grew to $364.3 million from $331 million in the year-earlier period. 
Comparable-store sales dipped 3% from the first half of fiscal 1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
