<HEADLINE>
<P>
AK-SAR-BEN POSTS ATTENDANCE DROP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
OMAHA 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ak-Sar-Ben ended its 85-day meet Sunday with a 27% decline in attendance from 
the previous year and a 32% drop in mutuel handle. 
</P>
<P>
"We couldn't take another year like this," said Executive Director Don Drew 
said. "If we are down this much next year, it would effectively kill racing in 
Omaha, Nebraska." 
</P>
<P>
The overall attendance this season, which includes simulcasting outlets, was 
601,517. That was 27.1% lower than the 1989 total of 825,371. On-track 
attendance of 444,236 was 32.4% lower than last year's total of 657,167. 
</P>
</TEXT>
