<P>
STALIN'S GRANDSON TO PORTRAY HIM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MOSCOW 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The grandson of Josef Stalin will portray the late dictator in a new Soviet 
film about World War II, the Communist Party newspaper Pravda reported today. 
</P>
<P>
It said Yevgeny Djugashvili, a professor at a military academy, has agreed to 
take the part in "War Is War for Everyone" after long refusing to do so. 
</P>
<P>
The film covers the life of Stalin's son Yakov -- Djugashvili's father -- who 
was captured by the Nazis and offered in exchange for high-ranking German 
officers. 
</P>
<P>
Stalin, whose real name was Josef Vissarionovich Djugashvili, refused the 
offer, saying: "We do not exchange generals for soldiers." 
</P>
<P>
Yakov is assumed to have died in a German prison camp. 
</P>
<P>
The new film will star Zaza Kolelishvili, a well-known Georgian actor, as 
Yakov. 
</P>
